      "target": {
        "kind": "pull_request",
        "title": "#92684 fix(doctor): skip empty parent groupAllowFrom warning when all accounts override",
        "body": "## Summary\n\n`openclaw doctor` warns about an empty top-level `groupAllowFrom` even when every child account has its own populated `groupAllowFrom`. The runtime resolves `account ?? parent`, so the parent's empty list is never read — the warning is a false positive.\n\n**Root cause:** `scanEmptyAllowlistPolicyWarnings()` checks the parent channel config independently of its child accounts. When the parent's `groupPolicy` is `\"allowlist\"` but `groupAllowFrom` is empty, it warns — without checking whether every account under it already supplies its own list.\n\n**Fix:** Before emitting the parent-level group-allowlist warning, check whether **all** child accounts have their own populated `groupAllowFrom`. If they do, skip the parent warning (the parent scope is just a fallback that's never reached). DM-policy warnings at the parent scope are preserved.\n\n## Real behavior proof\n\n**Behavior or issue addressed:** `openclaw doctor` false-positive warning when top-level `groupAllowFrom` is empty but every account overrides it with its own populated list.\n\n**Real environment tested:** Linux 4.19.112, Node.js v24.13.1 via tsx, openclaw workspace importing the production `scanEmptyAllowlistPolicyWarnings` module.\n\n**Exact steps or command run after this patch:**\n```\n$ npx tsx repro-92684.ts\n\n=== Test 1: All accounts override parent groupAllowFrom (no false warning) ===\nWarnings: []\nNo false warning: PASS\n\n=== Test 2: Some accounts lack groupAllowFrom (should still warn) ===\nWarnings: [\"- channels.signal.groupPolicy is ...\"]\nHas parent warning: PASS\n\n=== Test 3: DM policy warnings preserved ===\nWarnings: [\"- channels.signal.dmPolicy is ...\"]\nDM warning preserved: PASS\n```\n\n**Evidence after fix:**\n```\nTest 1 — all accounts override → no false warning:          PASS\nTest 2 — some accounts lack → parent warning preserved:     PASS\nTest 3 — DM warnings untouched by the change:               PASS\n```\n\n**Observed result after fix:** Parent-level group-allowlist warning is suppressed when every child account carries its own populated `groupAllowFrom`. DM-policy warnings at the parent scope continue to fire. When even one account lacks its own list, the parent warning is preserved.\n\n**What was not tested:** Integration with specific channel plugins (signal, telegram, discord, etc.). The fix operates at the shared `scanEmptyAllowlistPolicyWarnings` layer before plugin-specific hooks fire, so it applies uniformly.\n\n## Test plan\n\n- [x] `pnpm vitest run src/commands/doctor/shared/empty-allowlist-scan.test.ts` — 5 passed\n- [x] `pnpm vitest run src/commands/doctor/shared/empty-allowlist-policy.test.ts` — 4 passed\n- [x] Regression: empty parent + all accounts override → no warning\n- [x] Regression: empty parent + some accounts lack → warning preserved\n- [x] Regression: DM warnings preserved at parent scope\n",
        "branch": "fix/issue-92684-doctor-empty-allowlist",
